805
01:09:47.770 --> 01:09:48.753
- Ah heavens.

806
01:09:49.680 --> 01:09:52.020
Is it possible a young
maid's witch be as mortal


807
01:09:52.020 --> 01:09:53.352
as an old man's life?

808
01:09:54.904 --> 01:09:57.487
(gentle music)

809
01:10:06.563 --> 01:10:08.646
- There's fennel for you.

810
01:10:12.720 --> 01:10:13.970
And columbines.

811
01:10:15.757 --> 01:10:19.363
That's for infidelity.

812
01:10:30.800 --> 01:10:32.357
There's rue for you.

813
01:10:35.523 --> 01:10:37.883
That's for repentance.

814
01:10:43.784 --> 01:10:46.990
I would give you some
violets for faithfulness but,


815
01:10:46.990 --> 01:10:50.393
they withered when my father died.

816
01:10:51.759 --> 01:10:53.280
- Oh God.

817
01:10:53.280 --> 01:10:55.093
- Come with me, my child.

818
01:10:56.340 --> 01:10:58.740
- Come, my coach.

819
01:10:58.740 --> 01:11:00.340
Goodnight ladies.

820
01:11:00.340 --> 01:11:02.953
Goodnight, sweet ladies.

821
01:11:03.800 --> 01:11:04.850
Goodnight (laughing).

822
01:11:05.740 --> 01:11:06.573
Goodnight.

823
01:11:07.443 --> 01:11:09.610
Goodnight.

824
01:11:09.610 --> 01:11:13.253
- By heaven, her madness will be revenged.

825
01:11:13.253 --> 01:11:15.753
(tense music)

826
01:11:19.610 --> 01:11:20.443
- My Lord.

827
01:11:23.758 --> 01:11:26.200
I have a letter here from Lord Hamlet

828
01:11:26.200 --> 01:11:27.663
delivered by sailor.

829
01:11:34.707 --> 01:11:36.146
- "Reverent King,

830
01:11:36.146 --> 01:11:38.737
"know that I've returned to your kingdom.

831
01:11:38.737 --> 01:11:41.316
"I ask your pardon and
beg leave to see you,


832
01:11:41.316 --> 01:11:46.287
"when I shall explain the
circumstances of my return."


833
01:11:48.369 --> 01:11:50.000
- Do you recognize the writing?

834
01:11:50.000 --> 01:11:51.753
- It's clearly Hamlet's hand.

835
01:11:54.420 --> 01:11:55.253
Leave us.

836
01:11:57.016 --> 01:11:59.516
(tense music)

837
01:12:00.490 --> 01:12:03.390
- It cures the
very sickness in my heart

838
01:12:03.390 --> 01:12:05.740
that I shall live to
tell him face to face,


839
01:12:05.740 --> 01:12:07.663
you are a dead man.

840
01:12:08.709 --> 01:12:12.500
- If he comes back,
what would you undertake


841
01:12:12.500 --> 01:12:14.959
to show yourself your father's son,

842
01:12:14.959 --> 01:12:17.000
in deed as well in word?

843
01:12:17.000 --> 01:12:19.570
- I'd cut his throat in church.

844
01:12:19.570 --> 01:12:23.070
- If he returns, 
I shall devise his death

845
01:12:23.070 --> 01:12:26.450
in such a way
shall not fail to fall

846
01:12:26.450 --> 01:12:28.640
and make it all look like an accident.

847
01:12:28.640 --> 01:12:31.560
So even Gertrude will not know the truth.

848
01:12:31.560 --> 01:12:34.420
- And I will be
the agent of his fall.

849
01:12:34.420 --> 01:12:38.350
- If he returns, I'll
praise your swordsmanship


850
01:12:38.350 --> 01:12:41.070
and challenge him to
meet you in a bout.

851
01:12:41.070 --> 01:12:44.270
I'll make a wager he shall outdo you.

852
01:12:44.270 --> 01:12:47.750
He, unsuspecting, will not
notice if you use a foil


853
01:12:47.750 --> 01:12:49.923
whose tip you have unblunted.

854
01:12:51.277 --> 01:12:56.277
And thus, you shall revenge
your father's death.


855
01:12:57.240 --> 01:12:59.030
- Hell, when I unblunt my foil,

856
01:12:59.030 --> 01:13:00.360
I'll dip the point in poison

857
01:13:00.360 --> 01:13:02.330
I have brought with me from France.

858
01:13:02.330 --> 01:13:06.179
So mortal that a knife that's
dipped in it brings instant


859
01:13:06.179 --> 01:13:07.829
death with just a little scratch.

860
01:13:11.410 --> 01:13:16.153
- In case that fails,
we need a second plan.


861
01:13:17.270 --> 01:13:21.602
When from the bout, he
gets a little thirsty,


862
01:13:22.869 --> 01:13:27.403
I'll offer him a drink
that's tinged with poison.


863
01:13:30.097 --> 01:13:32.597
(tense music)

864
01:13:46.680 --> 01:13:49.430
(dramatic music)

865
01:13:55.090 --> 01:14:00.090
- [Hamlet] What is this
quintessence of dust?


866
01:14:05.319 --> 01:14:10.319
What is this quintessence
of dust, of dust, of dust?


867
01:14:18.700 --> 01:14:21.783
(tense guitar music)

868
01:14:27.277 --> 01:14:29.360
(thunder rumbles)

869
01:14:29.360 --> 01:14:32.997
- A spade, a spade, for
and a shrouding sheet.


870
01:14:32.997 --> 01:14:33.830
Oh, ah.

871
01:14:37.680 --> 01:14:40.223
Pit of clay shall soon be made,

872
01:14:41.170 --> 01:14:45.930
for my newest guest to greet.

873
01:14:45.930 --> 01:14:50.690
Oh, ah.
- Whose grave is this?


874
01:14:50.690 --> 01:14:51.553
- Mine, sir.

875
01:14:55.820 --> 01:14:57.119
- I think it yours indeed.

876
01:14:58.080 --> 01:14:59.523
For you lie in it.

877
01:15:00.550 --> 01:15:03.320
- You lie outside it, sir.

878
01:15:03.320 --> 01:15:05.493
Therefore it is not yours.

879
01:15:08.650 --> 01:15:11.369
I do not lie in it.

880
01:15:11.369 --> 01:15:14.298
And yet it is mine.

881
01:15:14.298 --> 01:15:16.548
(laughing)

882
01:15:17.539 --> 01:15:18.490
- You do lie in it.

883
01:15:19.730 --> 01:15:21.403
To be in it and say it's yours.

884
01:15:26.619 --> 01:15:28.360
It's for the dead.

885
01:15:28.360 --> 01:15:30.873
- Therefore you lie for all eternity.

886
01:15:33.510 --> 01:15:37.623
- Only the dead lie for all eternity.

887
01:15:37.623 --> 01:15:40.123
(tense music)

888
01:15:44.830 --> 01:15:47.410
- What man did you dig it for?

889
01:15:47.410 --> 01:15:48.660
- No man, sir.

890
01:15:48.660 --> 01:15:49.890
- What woman then?

891
01:15:49.890 --> 01:15:51.070
- None neither.

892
01:15:51.070 --> 01:15:53.119
- Who is it
to be buried in it?

893
01:15:53.119 --> 01:15:55.012
- One who was a woman,

894
01:15:56.180 --> 01:16:01.180
but knowingly drowned herself
and would have been denied


895
01:16:01.550 --> 01:16:04.110
Christian burial had
not she had been a lady


896
01:16:04.110 --> 01:16:06.623
of good birth and wealth.

897
01:16:17.910 --> 01:16:21.213
- How long have
you been a grave maker?

898
01:16:25.050 --> 01:16:28.970
- Since the very first day
that the young Lord Hamlet


899
01:16:28.970 --> 01:16:33.193
was born, he that is mad,

900
01:16:35.121 --> 01:16:36.583
and been sent to England.

901
01:16:37.709 --> 01:16:39.580
- Why was he sent to England?

902
01:16:39.580 --> 01:16:40.663
- Because he was mad.

903
01:16:42.030 --> 01:16:44.932
He shall recoup his wits there.

904
01:16:46.090 --> 01:16:48.663
If not, it makes no difference there.

905
01:16:51.850 --> 01:16:52.959
- Why?

906
01:16:52.959 --> 01:16:57.959
- Because all the men
there are as mad as he is.


907
01:17:01.300 --> 01:17:03.553
- How did he become mad?

908
01:17:05.280 --> 01:17:07.240
- By losing his wits.

909
01:17:07.240 --> 01:17:08.750
- Upon what ground?

910
01:17:08.750 --> 01:17:13.633
- Upon these grounds
right here in Denmark.


911
01:17:17.761 --> 01:17:21.650
- How long will a man live
in the earth before he rots?


912
01:17:24.060 --> 01:17:27.320
- If he's not rotten before he dies...

913
01:17:30.940 --> 01:17:33.063
we have many of those nowadays,

914
01:17:35.330 --> 01:17:38.143
it may last eight or nine years.

915
01:17:46.080 --> 01:17:50.193
Here's a skull that's been
laying in the earth for many-


916
01:17:51.238 --> 01:17:52.679
(thunder cracks)

917
01:17:52.679 --> 01:17:53.512
Years.

918
01:17:54.470 --> 01:17:55.610
- Whose was it?

919
01:17:55.610 --> 01:17:56.983
- This very skull sir?

920
01:18:00.101 --> 01:18:00.934
Who do you think?

921
01:18:00.934 --> 01:18:02.570
- I do not know.

922
01:18:02.570 --> 01:18:05.690
- This very skull was Yorick's skull.

923
01:18:05.690 --> 01:18:09.798
The King's jester.

924
01:18:09.798 --> 01:18:12.132
(chuckling)

925
01:18:13.250 --> 01:18:14.262
- Sir Yorick.

926
01:18:16.090 --> 01:18:18.090
- This?
- Yes.


927
01:18:18.090 --> 01:18:20.020
- Alas, poor Yorick.

928
01:18:20.020 --> 01:18:21.850
I knew him well.

929
01:18:21.850 --> 01:18:26.850
Fellow of infinite
jokes, flights of fancy.


930
01:18:28.150 --> 01:18:33.150
He bore me on
his back a thousand times.

931
01:18:33.250 --> 01:18:37.160
Here, upon those lips
I kissed as a child.

932
01:18:37.160 --> 01:18:38.233
I know not how often.

933
01:18:45.150 --> 01:18:46.773
Where be your jibes now?

934
01:18:48.410 --> 01:18:52.483
Your songs, your flashes of merriment,

935
01:18:53.590 --> 01:18:55.093
that made the courts roar.

936
01:18:56.220 --> 01:18:58.449
(thunder rumbling)

937
01:18:58.449 --> 01:19:01.032
(solemn music)

938
01:19:18.240 --> 01:19:23.240
- Lay her in the earth and
from her fair unpolluted flesh,


939
01:19:25.890 --> 01:19:27.247
may violets spring.

940
01:19:32.950 --> 01:19:35.033
- Sweets to the sweet.

941
01:19:37.470 --> 01:19:38.303
Farewell.

942
01:19:41.640 --> 01:19:43.740
I hoped you would have been Hamlet's wife.

943
01:19:47.690 --> 01:19:48.523
- Ophelia.

944
01:19:51.709 --> 01:19:55.060
- Devil take your soul.
- I loved Ophelia.


945
01:19:55.060 --> 01:19:56.100
- Love?

946
01:19:56.100 --> 01:19:57.340
Love you call it?

947
01:19:57.340 --> 01:19:58.740
- Take Hamlet away, Horatio.

948
01:20:01.425 --> 01:20:05.020
And you Gertrude, watch your son closely.

949
01:20:06.919 --> 01:20:09.502
(solemn music)

950
01:20:21.470 --> 01:20:23.223
We'll bring an end to this shortly.

951
01:20:24.792 --> 01:20:27.542
(thunder cracks)

952
01:20:37.396 --> 01:20:39.720
(thunder cracks)

953
01:20:39.720 --> 01:20:44.720
- There's a divinity that
shapes all of our ends.


954
01:20:51.217 --> 01:20:53.467
(grunting)

955
01:20:58.970 --> 01:21:01.903
- You will lose the wager, my Lord.

956
01:21:03.209 --> 01:21:04.993
- I shall win.

957
01:21:07.330 --> 01:21:10.123
But you can't imagine how I feel inside.

958
01:21:11.000 --> 01:21:14.310
- I'm gonna tell the king
you're not fit to fence.


959
01:21:14.310 --> 01:21:15.523
- No, no, no, no.

960
01:21:16.550 --> 01:21:19.583
We defy fate.

961
01:21:25.270 --> 01:21:30.270
There is a special providence
in the fall of the sparrow.


962
01:21:32.430 --> 01:21:33.953
If it be now-

963
01:21:35.730 --> 01:21:39.020
- Then it's not to come.

964
01:21:39.020 --> 01:21:40.633
- And if it be yet to come-

965
01:21:42.660 --> 01:21:45.297
- It will be now.

966
01:21:45.297 --> 01:21:48.510
- And if it be not now-

967
01:21:48.510 --> 01:21:50.983
- Yet, it will come.

968
01:21:51.820 --> 01:21:53.113
- Be ready for it all.

969
01:21:54.380 --> 01:21:57.283
- [Both] Just let it be.

970
01:21:58.316 --> 01:22:01.066
(dramatic music)

971
01:22:09.250 --> 01:22:11.743
- Come Hamlet, come
and take Laertes' hand.


972
01:22:20.270 --> 01:22:23.493
- Forgive the utter
rashness of my actions.


973
01:22:25.100 --> 01:22:30.100
Excuse my madness and accept my love.

974
01:22:30.709 --> 01:22:35.709
- I do receive your love
and I will not wrong it.


975
01:22:39.494 --> 01:22:40.328
- You know the wager?

976
01:22:40.328 --> 01:22:41.340
- I do.

977
01:22:41.340 --> 01:22:44.619
- If you should get the
first or second hit,


978
01:22:44.619 --> 01:22:47.343
the king shall drink to
Hamlet's princely skill.


979
01:22:57.700 --> 01:22:58.533
- My Lords.

980
01:23:05.175 --> 01:23:06.359
Begin!

981
01:23:06.359 --> 01:23:08.609
(grunting)

982
01:23:14.396 --> 01:23:17.217
(chuckling)

983
01:23:17.217 --> 01:23:19.467
(grunting)

984
01:23:21.916 --> 01:23:23.610
(laughing)

985
01:23:23.610 --> 01:23:24.543
- A touch.

986
01:23:25.930 --> 01:23:26.762
- A hit.

987
01:23:28.235 --> 01:23:29.235
A very palpable hit.

988
01:23:30.075 --> 01:23:32.325
(clapping)

989
01:23:34.180 --> 01:23:35.733
- Come, again.

990
01:23:37.459 --> 01:23:38.293
- Wait.

991
01:23:40.020 --> 01:23:42.953
Hamlet, have a drink.

992
01:23:46.830 --> 01:23:48.023
Come, just a sip.

993
01:23:50.070 --> 01:23:51.733
- I'll play this bout first.

994
01:23:58.220 --> 01:23:59.503
Come, Laertes.

995
01:24:06.155 --> 01:24:07.580
- Begin!

996
01:24:07.580 --> 01:24:09.830
(grunting)

997
01:24:16.778 --> 01:24:17.610
(laughing)

998
01:24:17.610 --> 01:24:18.444
- Another hit!

999
01:24:19.641 --> 01:24:20.990
What say you?
- A touch, a touch,


1000
01:24:20.990 --> 01:24:22.012
I do confess.

1001
01:24:23.090 --> 01:24:25.390
(clapping)

1002
01:24:25.390 --> 01:24:27.213
- Our son shall win.

1003
01:24:28.580 --> 01:24:31.573
- The queen salutes her
son with all her heart.


1004
01:24:39.260 --> 01:24:40.810
- I dare not drink yet, Mother.

1005
01:24:42.459 --> 01:24:43.293
Wait a while.

1006
01:24:47.190 --> 01:24:48.340
- To our son's victory.

1007
01:24:50.497 --> 01:24:52.997
(tense music)

1008
01:24:57.350 --> 01:24:59.863
- Come, for the third, Laertes.

1009
01:25:02.175 --> 01:25:03.516
(tense music)

1010
01:25:03.516 --> 01:25:06.266
(thunder cracks)

1011
01:25:12.118 --> 01:25:14.368
(grunting)

1012
01:25:21.777 --> 01:25:23.860
- What treachery is this?

1013
01:25:28.615 --> 01:25:29.448
- My son.

1014
01:25:30.535 --> 01:25:33.285
(dramatic music)

1015
01:25:46.455 --> 01:25:47.288
Poison.

1016
01:26:08.550 --> 01:26:09.893
- What treachery is this?

1017
01:26:11.230 --> 01:26:12.063
- Hamlet.

1018
01:26:14.830 --> 01:26:15.893
You are slain.

1019
01:26:20.940 --> 01:26:23.039
No medicine in the
world can save you now.

1020
01:26:24.539 --> 01:26:27.463
The treacherous instrument
was in your hand.


1021
01:26:32.280 --> 01:26:35.743
Unblunted and in venom,

1022
01:26:37.420 --> 01:26:42.420
the foul device has
now been turned on me.

1023
01:26:48.502 --> 01:26:49.334
And I die too.

1024
01:26:53.440 --> 01:26:57.813
I am justly killed by my own treachery.

1025
01:27:02.640 --> 01:27:03.789
Your mother's poisoned.

1026
01:27:07.884 --> 01:27:09.084
And the King's to blame.

1027
01:27:10.086 --> 01:27:12.836
(dramatic music)

1028
01:27:56.806 --> 01:27:58.389
- Follow my mother.

1029
01:28:14.846 --> 01:28:17.012
(gasping)

1030
01:28:18.785 --> 01:28:21.035
(shouting)

1031
01:28:22.108 --> 01:28:24.858
(dramatic music)

1032
01:28:50.682 --> 01:28:52.432
- Forgive me, Hamlet.

1033
01:28:55.338 --> 01:28:57.838
(tense music)

1034
01:29:32.363 --> 01:29:33.196
- My Lord.

1035
01:29:36.153 --> 01:29:37.343
- I may be dead,

1036
01:29:40.065 --> 01:29:41.015
but you'll live on.

1037
01:29:53.810 --> 01:29:54.873
- Not for long.

1038
01:30:00.490 --> 01:30:05.490
- If you ever did
love me, do not do it.

1039
01:30:12.030 --> 01:30:17.030
What's happened here
cannot be left unknown.


1040
01:30:22.800 --> 01:30:26.203
Tell my story.

1041
01:30:37.867 --> 01:30:39.534
The rest is silence.

1042
01:30:52.865 --> 01:30:55.032
(sobbing)

1043
01:31:26.385 --> 01:31:28.968
(gentle music)

1044
01:31:39.237 --> 01:31:42.580
- [Horatio] Let me speak
to the yet unknowing world,


1045
01:31:42.580 --> 01:31:44.182
how these things came about.

1046
01:31:46.760 --> 01:31:48.900
Bloody and unnatural acts

1047
01:31:50.650 --> 01:31:54.070
of deaths brought on by
evil, cunning and deceit,


1048
01:31:54.070 --> 01:31:57.030
all this will I truly tell.

1049
01:32:00.801 --> 01:32:03.301
(tense music)

1050
01:33:30.671 --> 01:33:33.253
(gentle music)

1051
01:35:46.696 --> 01:35:49.779
(gentle piano music)